      "message": "[🔴 Critical] Line 816: std::clamp is called with videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateMin as the lower bound and oldBitrate as the upper bound. If the current bitrate is already below the configured minimum, this violates std::clamp\u0027s precondition (lo \u003c\u003d hi), which is undefined behavior. Guard this case before clamping.\n```suggestion\n        if (oldBitrate \u003c\u003d videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateMin)\n            return;\n\n        newBitrate \u003d static_cast\u003cunsigned int\u003e(std::lround(static_cast\u003cfloat\u003e(oldBitrate) * reductionFactor));\n        newBitrate \u003d std::clamp(newBitrate, videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateMin, oldBitrate);\n```",
